item.title: Wizard of OZ Museum tour
item.description: Few people know that one of the only two Wizard of Oz Museums is right in Central Florida. Take advantage of this ticket to explore a hidden gem located near NASA and Cocoa Beach. Wander around the site where you’ll find an assortment of comic books, maps, dolls, collectibles, toys, posters, and other Wizard of Oz themed memorabilia. The museum even has original props and costumes from the movie.

image.alt: Wizard of OZ Museum tour

item.title: Cocoa Beach Aerial Adventures ticket
item.description: Visit Cocoa Beach Aerial Adventures, an aerial adventure park with dozens of fun and challenging obstacles. After a short “ground school” lesson to learn proper form and technique, it’s off to the ropes course, which includes suspension bridges, wide balance beams, tunnels, zip lines, balancing logs, monkey bars, and more. Make your way through all three levels of the course, with obstacles increasing in difficulty along the way.

image.alt: Cocoa Beach Aerial Adventures ticket

item.title: Port Canaveral to Orlando Airport MCO and Hotels Private Transfer
item.description: Simplify your arrival to Port Canaveral with a private transfer to Orlando Airport. After your cruise, meet a private driver at Port Canaveral and receive assistance with luggage. image.alt: Port Canaveral to Orlando Airport MCO and Hotels Private Transfer

item.title: Wizard of OZ Museum Ticket with Guided Tour by the Owner
item.description: Explore the Wizard of Oz Museum in Cape Canaveral with an admission ticket. Set out on a private tour of the museum with the owner, a collector of Wizard of Oz memorabilia. Learn about the owner’s collection and the stories behind the individual pieces on exhibit. Visitors will also have the option to examine an item from a special locked cabinet.

image.alt: Wizard of OZ Museum Ticket with Guided Tour by the Owner

item.title: Bioluminescence Kayak Tour Near Orlando
item.description: Florida is one of the few places in the world that hosts legendary bioluminescent organisms that light up the water at night. Kayak or canoe along the coast to see the waters flicker with every movement, and learn about the phenomenon from your guide on this tour from Cape Canaveral.

image.alt: Bioluminescence Kayak Tour Near Orlando

item.title: Dolphin & Manatee Kayaking Tour in Orlando Area
item.description: Explore the Indian River near Cocoa Beach on this guided, 2-hour kayaking tour. Choose from a selection of afternoon departures, then paddle through the warm waters and see local wildlife like Florida’s favorite manatees. These gentle giants are abundant here, friendly and curious with their surroundings – and any visitors. See how they spend their day, sunning themselves along the local coves and lagoons or gliding through the waterways. Kayaking gear and light refreshments are included on this small-group tour.

image.alt: Dolphin & Manatee Kayaking Tour in Orlando Area

item.title: Fully Guided Kayaking Backwater Manatee and Dolphin Tour
item.description: Spend a morning or afternoon kayaking the mangrove forests and tidal flats around Cape Canaveral. Departing from within walking distance of the cruise port, the tour is suitable for both experienced kayakers and first-timers—experienced guides are available the entire trip. Follow the calm, protected waters around the shoreline, keeping your eyes peeled for manatees, dolphins, otters, and many species of birds along the way.

image.alt: Fully Guided Kayaking Backwater Manatee and Dolphin Tour

item.title: Two Hour Private Surfing Lesson
item.description: Add “learning how to surf” to your checklist during your visit to the Kennedy Space Center. With 70+ miles (112+ kilometers) of beaches and reliable swells, Cape Canaveral is a fantastic place to learn the art of surfing. During this private lesson, your coach will get you in the water safely—and likely get you surfing on your own by the end of your time together.
